<div id="info-boxes">
  <div id="testbed-info" class="box">
    <h1 id="testbed-title" class="small-headline">The <span>AMazING</span> testbed</h1>
    <p id="testbed-description">
    The AMazING (Advanced Mobile wIreless Network playGround) consists of a free 
  access wireless testbed, composed by 24 fixed nodes located at IT Aveiro rooftop. 
  At the core of the testbed, there are the support servers and redundant storage. 
  Servers provide processing power to schedule, manage and analyze results. In the 
  near future we expect to extend the testbed with a high speed mobile node (>60km/h) 
  and integrate experiments with NS3.
    </p>
    <br/>
    <h1 id="platform-title" class="small-headline">About <span>AMazING Panel</span></h1>
    <p id="platform-description">
    The AMazING Panel consists on a Testbed Management System built on top of an OMF-enabled testbed. 
    The platform aims to provide easy-of-use for experimenters through a clean web interface, 
    facilitating the creation and reproducibility of their experiments, without 
    having much knowledge on the tools underneath.
    </p>

  </div>
  <div id="news" class="box">
    <h1 id="project-links-title" class="small-headline"><span>AMazING</span> Project</h1>
    <p id="project-links">
      AMazING Panel is a project in development that as some tools to assist in this matter.
      It has a website dedicated to the project which includes an issue tracker, a Wiki, a repository where
      the AMazING Panel source code is available and other relevant informations.
    </p>

   </br> </br>

